# Force LF for files that fail or break under CRLF when run inside a Linux
# container or invoked as executables. Editors on Windows hosts will save
# these as LF on checkout, and git will store LF on checkin regardless of
# the working-tree line endings.
#
# Symptoms this prevents:
#   * Shell scripts with CRLF shebangs fail with "cannot execute: required
#     file not found" (kernel hunts for `/bin/bash\r`).
#   * Dockerfile RUN heredocs and multi-line shell commands can fail with
#     CRLF inside container layers.
#   * TTS-server Python entrypoints baked into a Linux container.

*.sh             text eol=lf
Dockerfile       text eol=lf
/agent/dev       text eol=lf
tts-server/*.py  text eol=lf
